{
  "stem": "322.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they knew that I was in a-- you know, in Auschwitz, but that did not prevent them from, from drafting me and, and processing me, with one exception.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When it came to being sworn in, that was the time the swearing-in officer did say that is there anyone here who is not a citizen of the United States?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because before you're sworn in, you have a right not to serve or not to bear arms to defend the United States because you're not a citizen.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I can tell you, I was among maybe a dozen other survivors of death camps.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not one of them, not one of them said, no, I will not bear arms.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No, I will not defend the, the, you know, the United States.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We all did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we served.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I did not go to Korea.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Fortunately, they did not take me to Korea, but I did advance my studies at school.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In January of 1951, I became a, a regimental reporter, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and, and soon after that, when the regiment went back to Fort Meade, Maryland, I was selected for military intelligence.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And again, schooling.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This was perfect for me, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I had good schooling, even in the military.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I also went to preliminary-- well, leadership school, it was called, which was a preliminary officers candidate school, but I did not go into officers candidate schooling, because there was no more time left.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My, my two years expired, and that was it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I went back, back to New York, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] well, I was looking for a job.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I began to work, but I did not give up studying.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I went back to school.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
